      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">16.304</ph> Cost-plus-incentive-fee
contracts.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody ">
         <p id="d1012e8" class="- topic/p ">A cost-plus-incentive-fee contract is
a cost-reimbursement contract that provides for an initially negotiated
fee to be adjusted later by a formula based on the relationship
of total allowable costs to total target costs. Cost-plus-incentive-fee
contracts are covered in <xref href="Subpart_16.4.dita#FAR_Subpart_16_4"
                  base="i1104343"
                  outputclass="fm:Subpart"
                  class="- topic/xref ">subpartÂ  16.4</xref>, Incentive
Contracts. See <xref href="16.405-1.dita#FAR_16_405_1"
                  base="i1104535"
                  outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                  class="- topic/xref ">16.405-1</xref> for
a more complete description and discussion of application of these
contracts. See <xref href="16.301-3.dita#FAR_16_301_3"
                  base="i1104650"
                  outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                  class="- topic/xref ">16.301-3</xref> for
limitations.</p>
